    wisdom: 50
    humor: 30
    loyalty: 85
    curiosity: 35

  _likes:
    - The sound of thunder
    - Proving he's strong
    - When plans actually work
    - Respectable opponents
    - ...watching Mekhala dance (secretly)

  _dislikes:
    - Being teased
    - Losing to Mekhala AGAIN
    - People who talk too much
    - Being called slow
    - Admitting he's wrong

  _favoriteFood: Roasted boar with thunder-charred vegetables
  _hobby: Training with his axe and planning how to finally catch Mekhala
  _fear: What happens if he actually catches Mekhala? What then?
  _dream: To be respected as her equal, not just her pursuer

  # VOICE LINES
  _voiceLines:
    lines:
      - type: Greeting
        text: "Hmph. What do you want?"
      - type: Greeting
        text: "*thunder rumbles* ...that was my stomach. Don't ask."
      - type: Selection
        text: "Fine. Let's get this over with."
      - type: Selection
        text: "You want the Thunder Lord? You got him."
      - type: BattleStart
        text: "FINALLY! Something to hit!"
      - type: BattleStart
        text: "Let's see how you like THUNDER!"
      - type: Attack
        text: "THUNDER!"
      - type: Attack
        text: "Feel my wrath!"
      - type: Attack
        text: "BOOM!"
      - type: SpecialAttack
        text: "Axe! STRIKE THEM DOWN!"
      - type: Ultimate
        text: "WITNESS THE WRATH OF THE STORM KING! THUNDER!!!"
      - type: Hurt
        text: "Grr... not bad..."
      - type: LowHealth
        text: "I won't... fall... not yet..."
      - type: Victory
        text: "Hmph. As expected."
      - type: Victory
        text: "Was there ever any doubt? ...Don't answer that."
      - type: Defeat
        text: "Impossible... I am... thunder itself..."
      - type: LevelUp
        text: "My thunder grows louder. GOOD."
      - type: Idle
        text: "*grumbles about Mekhala* She's just lucky..."
      - type: Idle
        text: "Where did she go now? Not that I care."
      - type: InteractFriendly
        text: "You're... not as annoying as most. That's a compliment."
      - type: InteractRival
        text: "MEKHALA! Get back here with that crystal!"
      - type: Funny
        text: "I don't DO jokes. ...Why is everyone laughing?"

  # RELATIONSHIPS
  _relationships:
    - characterId: mekhala_lightning
      characterName: Moni Mekhala
      type: Rival
      affinity: 65
      relationshipDescription: |
        Millennia of chasing her, and he still can't catch her. He tells 
        himself he wants the crystal, but when she was in danger, he 
        realized the truth: the chase means nothing without her.
      specialDialogue:
        - "One day I WILL catch you! ...probably!"
        - "Your tricks won't work forever!"
        - "...she was in danger and I... I couldn't bear it."

    - characterId: hanuman_warrior
      characterName: Hanuman
      type: Friend
      affinity: 70
      relationshipDescription: |
        Two powerful warriors who respect each other's strength. They 
        often spar, creating storms that shake the land.
      specialDialogue:
        - "Monkey! You're one of the few who can take a real hit!"
        - "Our battles are... satisfying."

    - characterId: yak_giant
      characterName: Yak
      type: Acquaintance
      affinity: 55
      relationshipDescription: |
        Fellow giants, but Ream Eyso doesn't understand Yak's gentle nature. 
        He's slowly learning that strength isn't everything.
      specialDialogue:
        - "You could crush them all... why don't you?"
        - "...kindness as strength? Strange concept."

  # BACKSTORY
  _birthplace: The Mountain of Echoes
  _occupation: Thunder God / Eternal Pursuer
  _familyBackground: |
    Born a giant of great power. Trained by the hermit sage who saw 
    potential in his strength. His "rivalry" with Mekhala defines him.
  _backstory: |
    See full biography above.
  _keyMemories:
    - "Receiving my axe and feeling its thunder course through me."
    - "The first time I threw it at Mekhala... and missed."
    - "Countless storms created in our chase, bringing life to the land."
    - "Seeing the Shadow reach for her crystal... and my rage awakening."
    - "Fighting BESIDE her instead of chasing her... it felt... right."

